Note: CHEBYSHEV POLYNOMIALS OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "compute_chebyshev_first_kind" that takes n as Integer, x as Float, config as OrthogonalConfig returns PolynomialResult:
    Note: Compute Chebyshev polynomial of first kind T_n(x) = cos(n arccos x)
    Note: TODO: Implement T_n(x) with trigonometric definition and recurrence relations
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Chebyshev first kind not yet implemented"

Process called "compute_chebyshev_second_kind" that takes n as Integer, x as Float, config as OrthogonalConfig returns PolynomialResult:
    Note: Compute Chebyshev polynomial of second kind U_n(x) = sin((n+1) arccos x)/sin(arccos x)
    Note: TODO: Implement U_n(x) with trigonometric and algebraic representations
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Chebyshev second kind not yet implemented"

Process called "compute_chebyshev_zeros_first" that takes n as Integer returns List[Float]:
    Note: Compute zeros of T_n(x): x_k = cos((2k-1)π/(2n)) for k = 1,...,n
    Note: TODO: Implement first kind zeros with exact trigonometric formula
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Chebyshev first kind zeros not yet implemented"

Process called "compute_chebyshev_zeros_second" that takes n as Integer returns List[Float]:
    Note: Compute zeros of U_n(x): x_k = cos(kπ/(n+1)) for k = 1,...,n
    Note: TODO: Implement second kind zeros with trigonometric computation
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Chebyshev second kind zeros not yet implemented"

Process called "compute_chebyshev_extrema" that takes n as Integer returns List[Float]:
    Note: Compute extrema of T_n(x): x_k = cos(kπ/n) for k = 0,...,n
    Note: TODO: Implement extrema points for Chebyshev interpolation and approximation
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Chebyshev extrema not yet implemented"

Process called "apply_chebyshev_minimax_property" that takes n as Integer, interval as Dictionary[String, Float] returns Dictionary[String, Float]:
    Note: Apply minimax property of Chebyshev polynomials for optimal approximation
    Note: TODO: Implement minimax theorem with equioscillation and deviation bounds
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Chebyshev minimax property not yet implemented"

